<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/15900418-randy"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1369946250i/15900418._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/15900418-randy">Randy</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s written by an academic in a somewhat formal style for the adult reader of popular history. It&apos;s not an academic treatise; the book seeks to enter<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's written by an academic in a somewhat formal style for the adult reader of popular history. It's not an academic treatise; the book seeks to entertain as much as inform, to introduce the lay reader to the very different personal personal perspective on the world that was typical of those times. I think it succeeds in doing this.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
