        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer453212621" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13827714142481705325">One of the worst books I’ve ever read. it’s wrong, it’s wrong wrong wrong about so many things, it perpetuates this stagnated and antiquated notion of ~the dark ages~ for the sake of faux-humanist cynicism and it made me so speechlessly angry at its backward attitude towards the material. Did Manchester not pick up a book published since the Victorians? Contemporary scholarship left this shit in the dust decades ago; the fact that this book was published in the nineties is a disgrace. I am all f</span>
  <span id="freeText13827714142481705325" style="display:none">One of the worst books I’ve ever read. it’s wrong, it’s wrong wrong wrong about so many things, it perpetuates this stagnated and antiquated notion of ~the dark ages~ for the sake of faux-humanist cynicism and it made me so speechlessly angry at its backward attitude towards the material. Did Manchester not pick up a book published since the Victorians? Contemporary scholarship left this shit in the dust decades ago; the fact that this book was published in the nineties is a disgrace. I am all for accessible and exciting popular nonfiction. It’s practically my raison d’être! But it doesn’t follow that we have to sacrifice basic accuracy or intelligent analysis to get books in people’s hands; frankly, I find it insulting that it so dramatically underestimates the understanding and attention span of its audience. A pox on a world lit only by fire.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13827714142481705325" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
